//
// File: zannastudio/src/main.zia
// Purpose: Zanna Studio entry point, component construction, command routing, and
//          frame-loop orchestration.
// Key invariants:
//   - Input/render/process streams stay foreground responsive.
//   - Non-essential background work is throttled while the window is unfocused.
//   - App-level activation is requested after startup paints so native menu
//     ownership is available on macOS.
//   - Native resizing cannot collapse the workbench below a usable viewport.
//   - Split panes own distinct documents and pane focus drives tab selection.
//   - User-authored bottom-panel sizing is persisted only after drag input settles.
//   - Persistent activity views emit intent through their focused controllers.
//   - Edit chrome and command routing follow the active source or visual-scene
//     surface, including hierarchy-owned Find.
// Ownership/Lifetime:
//   - main owns every application controller until the frame loop exits.
//   - Cleanup drains process, worker, watcher, persistence, and GUI ownership.
// Links: zannastudio/src/ui/app_shell.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/app/lifecycle_controller.zia
//
//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

